-- Peru Stocks: Ferreyros, Grana y Montero, Maple Energy, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-02T19:00:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/peru-stocks-ferreyros-grana-y-montero-maple-energy-rio-alto.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:05 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  gained for the third session in
four, rising 0.6 percent to 23,118.84. The  MSCI All Peru Capped
Index (MXPECAPD)  fell 0.2 percent to 2,891.54.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
jumped 5.2 percent to $4.69 as investors bet the stock will gain
following expansion work at the company’s Peruvian mine, said
Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, climbed 2.3 percent to $1.33
after announcing it secured $17.5 million in financing for an
ethanol project.  Grana y Montero SA  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm known as GyM, gained 1.8 percent to a record
7.50 soles after the National Statistics Institute reported both
public spending and cement sales rose on construction demand in
January.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., rose for a fourth session, adding 1.3 percent
to 3.03 soles, on rising demand for mining equipment, Bustamante
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
